!! The Workbench

[centrifuge, alchemical liquids]

[WIP]

Trying to get up the table leg is tricky; the staircase suddenly becomes a slide and Arien/Dowin slide down to the bottom. If they try to climb, their hands might stick with pine sap.

Can potentially get here by leaping from the top of the larder to the [[cleansing stone]], then to a chair near the workbench, then onto the workbench. 

Alchemy mishaps: Things the potions on the alchemy workbench do when tipped over.

* The liquid creates an explosion of purple smoke that causes sneezing.
* The liquid immediately becomes thick, sticky, flammable webbing.
* The liquid forms into a tentacled [[ooze]] creature and scuttles away. It scrambles about, attacking any creature it comes into contact with, for 1 minute, after which it reverts to a normal liquid.
* The liquid emits fumes; any creature which inhales these fumes may fall under the effects of the spell [[confusion]].
* The liquid is extremely magnetic, pulling ferrous metal towards it.
* The liquid rapidly crystalizes, and sharp spikes protrude up from the surface.
* The liquid hisses and rapidly evaporates, leaving behind a grey, chalky precipitate.
* The liquid causes hair to grow rapidly on any creature on which it spills.
* The liquid causes any copper-based metals to rapidly patina on contact. The patina is greenish-blue, and causes the autotomtas to lose some mobility and dexterity.
* The liquid is a [[potion of healing]], and imparts low-impact [[magical healing]] upon contact with a living creature.

The centrifuge is a converted spinning wheel. If the party tries to get the motivation but the grig is still around, he'll hop on the spinning wheel and start pedaling, causing the centrifuge to spin while Arien/Dowin climbs on it.

!! The Grig's Song

!!! Stanza 1

“The tale of the tomtas of Clothiers Colworn,
Will fill one with laughter, even the forlorn!

The wee fey were eager to help with the chores,
To clean up the workshop, and organize drawers!

The fey wanted nothing in return except,
A saucer of porridge while the Colworns slept.

But one day, the well-meaning Mrs. did knit,
Small caps and small sweaters and left them as gifts.

The tomtas were outraged, and took great offense,
Preferring their nudeness, they quickly fled thence!

Distressed by this outcome, the Colworns addressed
The Mallow Inventor to help with this mess!

The warlock did puzzle, and ponder and brood,
To build a replacement for fey servitude.”

!!! Stanza 2

“The Mauve made a host of wee automatons,
Diminutive constructs made of burnished bronze.

These clockwork attendants were programmed to serve,
And nightly would tidy the workshop with verve.

Now, all of the tomtas, who hid in this shed,
Watched all this unfold with resentment and dread.

“How could they replace us?” the fey did bemoan,
And onto the Colworns’ chores, added their own.

They ordered the constructs to clean the workshop,
And fetch them fine trinkets and feed them gumdrops!

And thus the constructs became too occupied,
To fulfill the tasks for which they’d been designed.

They served the fat tomtas, met their every whim,
While I watched and laughed with mirth filled to the brim!”

!!! Stanza 3

“Before long, the tomtas grew restless and bored,
And sought to rebuild their old Colworn accord.

But I was unwilling to let the fun end,
Nor cast out the constructs, my new silly friends.

I played a soft dirge that was numbing and mild,
And all of the tomtas, they harkened and smiled.

The fey lay recumbent, with lead-lidded eyes,
And their motivation swiftly crystallized.

I snatched up this bauble, which shimmered surreal,
And hid it on top of a strange spinning wheel.

And lastly, I sealed up this shed like a fort,
To block any meddlers who’d spoil the sport!

So each day I laugh with my waltzing mouse chums,
At once-eager servants, turned do-nothing bums!”

!! Facing the Grig

The grig presents a riddle to the party. If they can guess his name, he'll release the seal and leave this place.

<<<
If you wish me to yield, simply tell me my name.
Very straightforward are the rules to my game.
Every sentence contains a clue in disguise.
Now look to the front within your mind’s eyes.
<<<

(Read the first letter of each line.)

<<<
You’ve determined my first name, well done, however,
Now guess my middle name, to prove you are clever!

Strange how words can have two meanings.
My middle name is also alive and breathing.
Perched in the trees, shrouded in black.
Intelligence is not something it lacks.
Four letters in total, one syllable is all.
My name can speak, but it mostly says “caw”.
<<<

(Crow.)

<<<
Excellent work, but you’re not done just yet.
My last name is tricky, guess that and you’re set!

For your final challenge, look for your cue,
And know that this riddle was made just for you.
Heed these words, look with more than your eye,
For in this message, five clues reside.
These clues the characters in my last name,
Made from words and letters that sound the same.
<<<

(Find the words that sound like letters when spoken aloud.)

